Suppose m \geq n, then we observe that \left |\left |{\widehat {\mathbf {A}}}_{r}-{\mathbf {A}}\right |\right |_{2}\;=\;\left |\left |\sum _{i=r+1}^{n}\sigma _{i}\mathbf {u}_{i}\mathbf {v}_{i}^{\mathsf {T}}\right |\right |_{2} \leq \sigma _{r+1}
Second, to prove our result, we want to show that \left |\left |\mathbf {B}_{r}-\mathbf {A}\right |\right |_{2}\ \geq \ \sigma _{r+1},\quad \forall \mathbf {B}_{r}\ \text {with}\ \mathrm {rank}(\mathbf {B}_{r})=r. We suppose \ \mathbf {B}_{r}=\widetilde {\mathbf {U}}\widetilde {\mathbf {V}}^{\top },\quad \widetilde {\mathbf {U}}\in \mathbb {R}^{m\times r},\ \widetilde {\mathbf {V}}\in \mathbb {R}^{n\times r}. Note
\begin {align*} ||\mathbf {B}_r - A||_2^2 &= \sup _{||\boldsymbol {z}||_2 \leq 1} ||(\mathbf {B}_r - \mathbf {A})\mathbf {z}||_2^2 \\ &\geq ||(\mathbf {B}_r - \mathbf {A})\mathbf {w}||_2^2 \end {align*}
Since \widetilde {V} has r columns, then there must be a nontrivial linear combination of the first r{+}1 columns of V, i.e., \mathbf {w}=\gamma _{1}\mathbf {v}_{1}+\cdots +\gamma _{r+1}\mathbf {v}_{r+1} such that \widetilde {V}^{\top }\mathbf {w}=\mathbf {0}\,. Wlog, we can scale \left |\left |\mathbf {w}\right |\right |_{2}=1 and \,\sum _{i=1}^{r+1}\gamma _{i}^{2}=1 Then ||\mathbf {A}-\mathbf {B}_{k}||_{2}^{2}\geq ||(\mathbf {A}-\mathbf {B}_{k})\,\mathbf {w}||_{2}^{2}=||\mathbf {A}\mathbf {w}||_{2}^{2}=\gamma _{1}^{2}\sigma _{1}^{2}+\cdots +\gamma _{r+1}^{2}\sigma _{r+1}^{2}\geq \sigma _{r+1}^{2}.

